info.description:
========================================================
pyrabbit.interim - Project templates for paster --create
========================================================

.. toctree::
   :maxdepth: 3

Quickstart
==========

Download and buildout pyrabbit.interim:

* git co git://github.com/snwilhelm/pyrabbit.interim.git
* cd pyrabbit.interim
* python bootstrap.py
* bin/buildout

After the buildout of pyrabbit.interim, you have the "paster" command in your
bin/ directory. Try it calling:

paster create -t interim_basepackage -o PATH_TO_PLACE_NEW_PROJECT

paster has now created a new project based on "interim_basepackage" for you.
You can change to PATH_TO_PLACE_NEW_PROJECT and redo the steps

* python bootstrap.py
* bin/buildout

now for your new project. Happy coding :-D

Feedbackup always!!!
